Boil a half-full #kettle{}.

Put the @couscous{120%g} in a #bowl{}.

Pour in the @boiled water for the couscous{200%ml}. Stir in half the @chicken stock paste{20%g}, then cover tightly with #cling film{}.

Leave to the side for ~{10%minutes}.

Next, heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a #frying pan{} on medium-high heat.

Once hot, fry the @diced British chicken breast{240%g}, ~{8-10%minutes}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. IMPORTANT: Wash hands and utensils after handling raw meat. Cook so there's no pink in the middle.

Meanwhile, open the remaining sachets.

Mix the @roasted spice and herb blend{1%sachet}, @tomato puree{30%g}, @water for the sauce{150%ml} and remaining chicken stock paste into the chicken.

Stir through the @honey{15%g} and @butter{20%g}. TIP: Pop hardened honey into hot water for 1 min.

Add the @baby spinach{40%g} in handfuls, making sure it's piping hot, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Fluff up the couscous with a #fork{}. Stir through the @zhoug style paste{45%g} (add less if you'd prefer things milder).

Share your couscous between #bowls{}.

Top with your spiced chicken. Finish with a dollop of @Greek style natural yoghurt{75%g}. Enjoy!